Definition 5.17. For any complex $A_{\bullet}=(A_{n},d_{n},\delta_{n})$ in $\mathbf{S}$, we put (1) $[Z^{n}(A_{\bullet}),z_{n}^{A},\zeta_{n}^{A}]:=\mathrm{Ker}(d_{n},\delta_{n+1})$. (2) $[Q^{n}(A_{\bullet}),q_{n}^{A},\rho_{n}^{A}]:=\mathrm{Cok}(d_{n-1},\delta_{n-1})$.
Definition 2.6. Let $f\in\mathbf{S}^{1}(A,B)$. (1) $f$ is said to be faithful if $f^{\flat}:=-\circ f:\mathbf{S}^{1}(C,A)\rightarrow\mathbf{S}^{1}(C,B)$ is faithful for any $C\in\mathbf{S}^{0}$. (2) $f$ is said to be fully faithful if $f^{\flat}$ is fully faithful for any $C\in\mathbf{S}^{0}$. (3) $f$ is said to be cofaithful if $f^{\sharp}:=f\circ-:\mathbf{S}^{1}(B,C)\rightarrow\mathbf{S}^{1}(A,C)$ is faithful for any $C\in\mathbf{S}^{0}$. (4) $f$ is said to be fully cofaithful if $f^{\sharp}$ is fully faithful for any $C\in\mathbf{S}^{0}$.
Definition 3.7. Let $\mathbf{S}$ be a locally $\mathrm{SCG}$ 2-category. $\mathbf{S}$ is said to be relatively exact if the following conditions are satisfied$:$ (B1) For any 1-cell $f\in\mathbf{S}^{1}(A,B)$, its kernel and cokernel exist. (B2) For any 1-cell $f\in\mathbf{S}^{1}(A,B)$, $f$ is faithful if and only if $f=\mathrm{ker}(\mathrm{cok}(f))$. (B3) For any 1-cell $f\in\mathbf{S}^{1}(A,B)$, $f$ is cofaithful if and only if $f=\mathrm{cok}(\mathrm{ker}(g))$. It is shown in [9] that $\mathrm{SCG}$ satisfies these conditions.
