Definition 2.8. For symmetric categorical groups $\mathbb{G}$ and $\mathbb{H}$, a monoidal functor $F$ from $\mathbb{G}$ to $\mathbb{H}$ consists of (a1) a functor $F:\mathbb{G}\rightarrow\mathbb{H}$ (a2) natural isomorphisms $F_{A,B}:F(A\otimes B)\rightarrow F(A)\otimes F(B)\ \text{and}\ F_{I}:F(0)\rightarrow 0$ which satisfy certain compatibilities with $\alpha$, $\lambda$, $\rho$, $\gamma$. $($cf. [5]$)$
